edu.rit.pj2.example

Class MinVerCovSmp2

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.rit.pj2.Task
      • edu.rit.pj2.example.MinVerCovSmp2

  • public class MinVerCovSmp2
extends Task
    Class MinVerCovSmp2 is an SMP parallel program that finds a minimum vertex cover of a graph via exhaustive search. The program reads the graph from a file. The graph format is as follows: The first line consists of V and E. Each subsequent line consists of two vertex numbers each in the range 0 through V−1, defining an edge between those vertices. The program's running time is proportional to 2V.

    Class MinVerCovSmp constructs a new object on every loop iteration. Class MinVerCovSmp2 reuses the same object on every loop iteration.

    Usage: java pj2 edu.rit.pj2.example.MinVerCovSmp2 file
    file = Graph file
